= Installing Git =
Git is a distributed control management software used by the [http://www.freedesktop.org freedesktop.org] to host its projects. In order to get the latest code available for the latest version or other code branches of APOC you need to use a Git client to fetch it. You can see more instructions on how to get the latest APOC source code on the [:Apoc/Downloads: download section].

[[TableOfContents()]]
== Git on Ubuntu/Debian ==
Look for the package git-core on the Synaptic package management tool, or typing this:
{{{
$ sudo apt-get install git-core
}}}

== Git on Fedora ==
Type this as root:
{{{
# yum install git-core
}}}

== Git on Solaris ==
To install Git on Solaris we provide a set of stream packages built from the [http://pkgbuild.sourceforge.net Spec Files Extra] repository. (Thanks to Laszlo Peters for the SFE project and the help on building the binary packages). Git depends on [http://curl.haxx.se/ curl], so you need to install the curl binary too.
